BT /F3 18 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 730 Tm (Preface) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 696 Tm (This book is for programmers who are new to Puff.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 682 Tm (It assumes you already know the basics of programming, but not the shape of ) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 668 Tm (this language. The goal is to get you productive quickly, without pretending ) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 654 Tm (Puff is larger than it is. Every chapter in this book is based on features ) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 640 Tm (that exist in the repository today.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 626 Tm (Puff is the public CLI and user-facing tool. `pinggen` is still the compiler ) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 612 Tm (and repository name you will see in source, docs, and internal implementation ) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 598 Tm (paths. In practice, you create, build, and run programs with `puff`.) Tj ET
BT /F3 18 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 584 Tm (Who Puff Is For) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 550 Tm (Puff is a good fit when you want:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 536 Tm (- a small compiled language with explicit project structure) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 522 Tm (- straightforward syntax for functions, structs, enums, and modules) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 508 Tm (- a minimal but useful standard library for CLI-style work) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 494 Tm (- native executables without a large runtime or framework) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 480 Tm (Puff is not trying to be everything yet. It is strongest today for:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 466 Tm (- command-line utilities) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 452 Tm (- file-processing tools) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 438 Tm (- code generators) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 424 Tm (- small automation programs) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 410 Tm (- experiments in language and compiler design) Tj ET
