BT /F3 18 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 716 Tm (1. What Puff Is and What It Is Good For) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 682 Tm (Puff is a compiled language built in C++ with a textual LLVM IR backend. ) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 668 Tm (Source files use the `.pg` extension. A Puff project is usually a directory ) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 654 Tm (with a `pinggen.toml` file and a `src/` folder containing one or more `.pg` ) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 640 Tm (modules.) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 626 Tm (The current language surface includes:) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 612 Tm (- typed top-level functions) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 598 Tm (- structs and methods) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 584 Tm (- enums with optional single payloads) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 570 Tm (- exhaustive `match`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 556 Tm (- tuples) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 542 Tm (- fixed-size arrays) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 528 Tm (- built-in dynamic vectors with `Vec<T>`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 514 Tm (- explicit modules and dependencies) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 500 Tm (- a small namespaced standard library) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 70 486 Tm (- a strict task-parallel `con { ... }` feature) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 472 Tm (Puff stays deliberately narrow. You get a compact language and a direct ) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 458 Tm (toolchain, not a large framework or a giant ecosystem.) Tj ET
BT /F3 18 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 444 Tm (2. Installing and Running `puff`) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 410 Tm (From the repository root, build the compiler with CMake:) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 396 Tm (cmake -S . -B build) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 383 Tm (cmake --build build) Tj ET
BT /F1 11 Tf 1 0 0 1 56 370 Tm (You can use the local launcher directly from the repo:) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 356 Tm (.\\puff help) Tj ET
BT /F2 10 Tf 1 0 0 1 68 343 Tm (.\\puff doctor) Tj ET
